15:33.920 --> 15:38.500
♪♪

15:38.500 --> 15:44.380
♪ Get my 40 acres and a mule ♪

15:45.880 --> 15:46.960
Josh: Wow.

15:46.960 --> 15:48.620
I had no idea,
Dre.

15:48.620 --> 15:50.580
Hey, I want to be onboard
with Juneteenth.

15:50.580 --> 15:52.250
I really do,

15:52.250 --> 15:54.080
but y-you have to admit it's
a confusing thing to celebrate.

15:54.080 --> 15:56.250
I mean, do I get you a card?
Do you get me a card?

15:56.250 --> 15:57.750
Stevens:
I don't know, Dre.

15:57.750 --> 16:00.830
It seems like a straight-up
conflict with Father's Day.

16:00.830 --> 16:02.580
[ Scoffs ]
In our community?

16:02.580 --> 16:04.790
[ Chuckles ] Eh, okay.

16:04.790 --> 16:06.880
And June is the beginning
of wedding season.

16:06.880 --> 16:07.880
In our community?

16:07.880 --> 16:09.540
[ Chuckles ] Eh, okay.

16:09.540 --> 16:11.330
Dre: I'm only
hearing excuses.

16:11.330 --> 16:14.380
This is what America
always does.

16:14.380 --> 16:16.790
We think if we don't
acknowledge something awful,

16:16.790 --> 16:18.380
it didn't happen.

16:18.380 --> 16:21.210
Sure, Columbus' men
cut the hands off of people

16:21.210 --> 16:23.380
and made them
wear them around their neck,

16:23.380 --> 16:25.250
but no,
let's not talk about that

16:25.250 --> 16:27.670
because that happened
so long ago.

16:27.670 --> 16:29.620
Stevens: Wow, Dre,
you are all over the place.

16:29.620 --> 16:30.830
Aloe Blacc:
He's right.

16:30.830 --> 16:32.080
I mean,
you got me over here

16:32.080 --> 16:33.620
drawing logos,
singing songs,

16:33.620 --> 16:36.460
posting facts about slavery
from my personal Instagram.

16:36.460 --> 16:38.380
Wh--
Where are you going
with this here?

16:38.380 --> 16:40.000
I mean,
what do you want?

16:40.000 --> 16:41.170
What...

16:43.580 --> 16:45.380
What do I want?

16:45.380 --> 16:47.670
It...
What do I want?

16:47.670 --> 16:48.830
You know what?

16:48.830 --> 16:50.710
I'm tired
of wasting my breath on y'all.

16:50.710 --> 16:52.000
I'm out.

16:54.420 --> 16:55.460
Dre's right.

16:55.460 --> 16:57.210
You guys' behavior
is unacceptable.

16:57.210 --> 16:58.540
I'm out, too.

16:58.540 --> 17:01.170
And not just because I have
a 3:00 flight to Oakland

17:01.170 --> 17:03.170
for an "Electric Slide"
convention.

17:03.170 --> 17:09.790
♪♪

17:09.790 --> 17:11.790
Stevens: Aloe, I've been meaning
to tell you, uh,

17:11.790 --> 17:13.330
I-I love your song
"I'm Happy."

17:13.330 --> 17:14.830
Josh: Oh, no,
that's -- that's --

17:14.830 --> 17:16.210
Hmm?

17:16.210 --> 17:17.420
You know, I even know this.
That's the other guy.

17:22.380 --> 17:23.790
Here's an invitation
for our school talent show.

17:23.790 --> 17:25.460
Ooh!
It's for you.

17:25.460 --> 17:27.000
Alone.
Rainbow: Huh?

17:27.000 --> 17:29.290
No guests.
Do not
bring your husband.

17:29.290 --> 17:30.710
Uh...

17:30.710 --> 17:34.790
Okay, guys, guys, your dad
deserves a second chance.

17:34.790 --> 17:37.080
Maybe he will behave.

17:37.080 --> 17:39.170
You don't really
believe that.

17:40.210 --> 17:42.880
I don't.
That's what we thought.

17:42.880 --> 17:44.210
[ Door closes ]

17:44.210 --> 17:45.460
I just
have to say it, though.

17:45.460 --> 17:46.710
Hey.

17:46.710 --> 17:48.290
What's wrong
with you, son?

17:48.290 --> 17:49.750
You look like
somebody stole your lunch money.

17:49.750 --> 17:50.500
Dre:
Come on, Pops.

17:50.500 --> 17:51.960
Not now.

17:51.960 --> 17:53.750
I just realized
how much people don't like us.

17:53.750 --> 17:55.000
Oh!

17:55.000 --> 17:56.420
You just now
realizing that?

17:56.420 --> 17:57.670
You know those guys
at the office

17:57.670 --> 17:59.380
would rather work
than celebrate Juneteenth?

17:59.380 --> 18:00.540
Juneteenth?

18:00.540 --> 18:02.210
Dre, when did Juneteenth
become important to you?

18:02.210 --> 18:03.960
You don't even
celebrate Kwanzaa.

18:03.960 --> 18:05.750
That's because they make us
feel like it's wack.

18:05.750 --> 18:08.420
They make us feel like
all of our stuff is wack.

18:08.420 --> 18:09.500
Kwanzaa is wack!

18:09.500 --> 18:10.920
I know the guy
who invented Kwanzaa.

18:10.920 --> 18:12.580
Owes me $35.

18:12.580 --> 18:14.040
Pops,
think about it.

18:14.040 --> 18:16.120
Kwanzaa is no crazier
than Christmas.

18:16.120 --> 18:17.750
What's that you say
about Christmas?

18:17.750 --> 18:20.960
Okay, look, I will admit
this Juneteenth thing

18:20.960 --> 18:23.830
started out as a rant,
but it got me thinking.

18:23.830 --> 18:25.920
As much as I love
the 4th of July,

18:25.920 --> 18:28.000
shouldn't the real
Independence Day

18:28.000 --> 18:29.790
be the day
that everybody was free?

18:29.790 --> 18:31.210
Pops:
[ Chuckling ] Oh!

18:31.210 --> 18:33.040
You trying to take away
their illegal fireworks

18:33.040 --> 18:35.790
and a four-day weekend?

18:35.790 --> 18:38.790
You must be trying
to start a race war, son.

18:38.790 --> 18:42.580
I'm just saying I'm tired
of justifying our stuff.

18:42.580 --> 18:43.880
Irish people --

18:43.880 --> 18:45.210
They don't beg us
to celebrate St. Patrick's Day.

18:45.210 --> 18:46.580
Well, Dre,

18:46.580 --> 18:49.880
that's because leprechauns
and green beer are fun.

18:49.880 --> 18:52.210
Slavery isn't easy
to talk about.

18:52.210 --> 18:55.420
I mean, it makes people
uncomfortable.

18:55.420 --> 18:57.580
Mm, white people hate
being uncomfortable.

18:57.580 --> 19:00.380
Mm.
That's why they invented
those Rockports.

19:00.380 --> 19:03.460
[ Laughing ]
You know, them shoes. Yeah.

19:03.460 --> 19:06.290
We do so much already
to make them feel comfortable.

19:06.290 --> 19:08.040
We change
the way we talk.

19:08.040 --> 19:09.790
We straighten
our hair.

19:09.790 --> 19:12.000
We watch "Portlandia."
Ooh.

19:12.000 --> 19:14.040
I love that show.
Yeah.

19:14.040 --> 19:18.170
We do everything we can do
to turn down our blackness.

19:18.170 --> 19:20.080
Well, we're never gonna
not have to do that, son.

19:20.080 --> 19:22.920
Look, people are never
gonna celebrate something

19:22.920 --> 19:25.250
they barely even want
to admit happened.

19:25.250 --> 19:27.790
Look, I get that,
but at least

19:27.790 --> 19:31.080
can we have one day where
the country acknowledged it?

19:31.080 --> 19:35.880
It would feel like --
I don't know, an apology.

19:35.880 --> 19:37.000
Wow,
can you imagine that?

19:37.000 --> 19:38.290
Oh, hell, no.

19:38.290 --> 19:40.750
Instead of waiting
for an apology,

19:40.750 --> 19:42.330
why don't we just
do something?

19:42.330 --> 19:44.830
I mean, if we want to honor
the end of slavery,

19:44.830 --> 19:46.880
then we should celebrate
Juneteenth.

19:46.880 --> 19:49.250
Zoey: Wait, that's what
Juneteenth is.

19:49.250 --> 19:51.380
We don't celebrate
the end of slavery,

19:51.380 --> 19:53.380
but you wake us up early
on Cyber Monday?

19:53.380 --> 19:54.500
[ Zoey scoffs ]

19:54.500 --> 19:56.040
You are
a bad black person.

19:56.040 --> 19:57.040
Yeah.

19:57.040 --> 19:58.960
You know what?

19:58.960 --> 20:00.880
Not anymore.

20:00.880 --> 20:05.710
From now on,
we will be black out loud.

20:05.710 --> 20:08.670
Rainbow: Oh!
Our whole family
will celebrate Juneteenth.

20:08.670 --> 20:10.290
Ruby:
All right.
Boom!

20:10.290 --> 20:11.960
I know where to buy
strawberry soda.

20:11.960 --> 20:14.500
And I make a mean
red-velvet cake!

20:14.500 --> 20:16.040
I'll fire up the grill.
That loud and black
enough for you?

20:16.040 --> 20:17.380
Yeah.
Mm-hmm.

20:17.380 --> 20:18.580
I'll hang up
my stocking.

20:18.580 --> 20:20.210
♪♪

20:20.210 --> 20:21.710
Oh, buddy.

20:21.710 --> 20:22.880
Mm.
What?

20:26.580 --> 20:27.580
♪ Oh ♪

20:27.580 --> 20:28.960
♪ Oh ♪

20:28.960 --> 20:31.210
So we were a little late
this year,

20:31.210 --> 20:35.330
but the Johnson family
finally celebrated Juneteenth.

20:35.330 --> 20:38.420
And as much
as I want it to catch on,

20:38.420 --> 20:41.580
maybe all we can do
is try to heal ourselves.

20:41.580 --> 20:43.080
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

20:43.080 --> 20:46.920
So when America's finally ready
to truly apologize,

20:46.920 --> 20:49.960
hopefully we'll be ready
to forgive them.

20:49.960 --> 20:51.750
♪ Oh ♪

